<div class="row">
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<div class="recipe-modal-img-container">
			<img src="${pageContext.request.contextPath}/recipes/Crack_Slaw.jpg" />
		</div>
		<h4>Ingredients</h4>
		<ul class="ingredients">
			<li>8 ounces lean ground beef</li>
			<li>4 cups cabbage, or broccoli slaw</li>
			<li>1 raw scallion (green onion)</li>
			<li>2 cloves minced garlic</li>
			<li>2 ​T​bsp Soy Sauce</li>
			<li>1/2 Tbsp sesame oil</li> 
			<li>1 tsp crushed red pepper flakes</li>
			<li>2 tsp splenda</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<h4>Instructions</h4>
		<ol class="instructions">
			<li>Cut up the scallion into small 1/4 inch pieces.</li>
			<li>Over medium-high heat, Brown the ground beef with the garlic and crushed red pepper -  do not drain</li>
			<li>Reduce heat to medium, stir in cabbage. Once mixed well, add soy sauce and cook for 3 - 4 min</li>
			<li>Once the cole slaw mix gets tender, add the  Splenda, scallion, and sesame oil. Mix well and cook for 1 more minute.</li> 
		</ol>
	</div>
</div>